지금 춥지 않아요  It’s not cold now
촙지 않을 거예요  It won’t be cold
지금 필요하지 않아 I don’t need need it now
필요하지 않았어요 I didn’t need it
일하다 (to work) 쉬다 (to take a break, to rest)
(Time) 에 (place) 에서 일하아 :: to work at a (place) at (time)
마침밥 같이 먹을까요? :: shall we eat breakfast together?
어디까지 갈까요? :: How far shall we go?
뭐를 살까요?  What shall I buy
지금 먹을까 :: I wonder if I should eat now
일할까?  :: I wonder if I should work
공주할까? :: I wonder if I should study
점심밥을 먹읍시다 ::  Let’s eat lunch

팥죽 할머니와 호랑이
Red porridge, grand mother and the lion
옛날옛날 깊은 산속에 꼬부랑 할머니가 살았어요
A long time ago, an old grandmother lived deep in the mountains
어느 여름날 할머니는 팥밭을 맸어요
One summer day, my grandmother put on a red bean field.
여름 : Summer
팥밭 한 고랑을 매고는 "애고, 힘들어"
In one red bean field, she said “Oh, I’m tired”
팥밭 두 고랑을 매고는 "애고 애고 힘들어"
In the second red bean field she siad, “oh, oh, I am tired”
팥밭 세 고랑을 매고는 “애거, 애고, 애고, 힘들어 ”
In the third red bean field she said “oh, oh, oh, I am tired”
겁자기: suddenly all of a sudden
나타나다: appear, turn up, show
그때 갑자기 커다란 호랑이가 나타났어요,
Then suddenly a tiger appeared

사람 살려!
Save me!
말하다 : To say, speak, talk
호랑이가 입을 떠억 벌리며 말했어요
The tiger spoke with his mouth open

